    <p>UNIQLO RE­OPENS AT ION OR­CHARD</p>
    <p>Af­ter its head­line-grab­bing queues last Fri­day at Or­chard Cen­tral for its lat­est col­lab­o­ra­tion with Ger­man fash­ion de­signer Jil San­der, Uniqlo has more up its sleeve.</p>
    <p>The newly ren­o­vated store at Ion Or­chard re­opens to­day, with an in-store mu­ral about Or­chard Road by lo­cal vis­ual artist Michael Ng (right), who goes by Mind­flyer.</p>
    <p>There are plans to change the art­work con­tin­u­ally over the months, to show­case the works of other Sin­ga­porean artists.</p>
    <p>New to the store is a ded­i­cated UT Zone for Uniqlo’s ex­ten­sive range of graphic tees and an Airism Bed­ding corner where cus­tomers can feel the bed­ding goods.</p>
    <p>From to­day to Sun­day, the first 200 cus­tomers to spend a min­i­mum of $80 in a sin­gle re­ceipt in-store will re­ceive a tote bag de­signed by Mind­flyer.</p>
    <p>Also launch­ing to­day is a lim­it­ededi­tion hol­i­day cap­sule col­lec­tion with Marimekko – Uniqlo’s fourth col­lab­o­ra­tion with the Fin­nish de­sign house.</p>
    <p>The cap­sule in­cludes warm dresses ($29.90 to $59.90) and Ul­tra Light Down out­er­wear ($129.90 to $199.90) in sig­na­ture Marimekko prints, and will be avail­able on­line and at se­lected Uniqlo stores.</p>
    <p>Info: Uniqlo Ion Or­chard is lo­cated at B2-01/38 and B3-51/52, Ion Or­chard, 2 Or­chard Turn</p>

